Spots can be seen about one and a half miles out into the sea outside the big municipality Hillsborough, but in fewer places compared to last week.
Algflowering has also been observed in the large municipality of Pasco.
Medium concentrations in or off the coast of Pinellas have been reported during the past week. Outside Hillsboroughs coast low to high concentrations, background concentrations to high concentrations in Manatee, background concentrations to high concentrations in or off the coast of Sarasota, background concentrations to medium concentrations in or off the coast of Lee, and low concentrations in Collier.
Reports of respiratory irritation continue to come from the major municipalities of Pinellas, Manatee, Sarasota, Lee and Collier.
There were no reports of respiratory irritation in northwestern Florida this past week.
